@startuml "Application State Machine - Diagram"

!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #ffffff
skinparam defaultFontName monospace
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam stateBorderColor #333333
skinparam stateBackgroundColor #fff4e6
skinparam arrowColor #333333

title "Application State Machine (AppMode) with RigEngine"

state "Normal" as Normal {
    Idle state
    Ready for user input
    Terminal display live
}

state "WaitingLLM" as WaitingLLM {
    Querying LLM backend
    Terminal frozen
    Animated throbber
}

state "AwaitingApproval" as AwaitingApproval {
    LLM provided command
    Waiting for y/n response
    Command displayed
}

state "ExecutingCommand" as ExecutingCommand {
    Command approved by user
    Executing in PTY
    Capturing output
}

state "AwaitingAnswer" as AwaitingAnswer {
    LLM asked question
    Waiting for text input
    Question displayed
}

' From Normal
Normal --> WaitingLLM : QueryLLM\n(user typed ? query)

' From WaitingLLM
WaitingLLM --> Normal : LLMCompleted\n(no further action)

WaitingLLM --> AwaitingApproval : LLMRequestsApproval\n{ command, message }\n(RigEngine tool call)

WaitingLLM --> AwaitingAnswer : LLMAsksQuestion\n{ question, options }\n(RigEngine asks for input)

' From AwaitingApproval
AwaitingApproval --> ExecutingCommand : UserApprovedCommand\n(user pressed y)

AwaitingApproval --> Normal : Cancel\n(user pressed n or Ctrl+C)

' From ExecutingCommand (new in RigEngine)
ExecutingCommand --> WaitingLLM : CommandExecuted\n(needs_continuation=true)\nOutput sent to agent
ExecutingCommand --> Normal : CommandExecuted\n(needs_continuation=false)\nOutput is final answer

' From AwaitingAnswer
AwaitingAnswer --> WaitingLLM : UserAnswered\n(user typed answer + Enter)

AwaitingAnswer --> Normal : Cancel\n(Ctrl+C - abort question)

' From WaitingLLM (cancel)
WaitingLLM --> Normal : Cancel\n(Ctrl+C - abort LLM query)

' Idempotent transition
Normal --> Normal : Cancel\n(idempotent)

note right of Normal
    **Default state:**
    - User can type commands
    - PTY output displayed
    - Cursor visible
    - All input modes available
end note

note right of WaitingLLM
    **LLM Query in Progress:**
    - Terminal output frozen
    - Animated throbber shows wait state
    - User can press Ctrl+C to cancel
    - Streaming response display
end note

note right of AwaitingApproval
    **Command Approval Needed (HITL):**
    - LLM command shown
    - Explanation displayed
    - Waiting for y/n/Ctrl+C
    - RigEngine: triggered by execute_shell_command tool call
end note

note right of ExecutingCommand
    **Command Executing (NEW):**
    - User approved execution
    - Command runs in PTY
    - Output captured
    - Agent decides next step via needs_continuation
    - If true: agent continues with output
    - If false: output is final answer
end note

note right of AwaitingAnswer
    **LLM Question Needs Answer:**
    - Question displayed
    - Free-text or multiple choice
    - Waiting for user input + Enter
    - RigEngine: triggered by ask_user tool call
end note

note bottom
    **State Machine Properties:**

    1. **Valid Transitions Only:**
       - can_transition_to(target) checks validity
       - Invalid transitions return error
       - Prevents corrupted state

    2. **Atomic Transitions:**
       - transition(event) consumes self + event
       - Returns new state or error
       - No intermediate states

    3. **RigEngine HITL Flow:**
       - Tools intercept before execution
       - AwaitingApproval → ExecutingCommand (new)
       - needs_continuation flag controls next state
       - ExecutingCommand → WaitingLLM or Normal

    4. **Cancel from Most States:**
       - Cancel always → Normal (except Normal itself)
       - Ctrl+C provides user escape hatch

    **Implementation:**
    pub enum AppMode {
        Normal,
        WaitingLLM,
        AwaitingApproval { command, message },
        AwaitingAnswer { question, options },
        ExecutingCommand { command },
    }

    **RigEngine Specific:**
    ExecutingCommand state NEW with RigEngine
    Captures command output for needs_continuation decision
end note

@enduml
